SPELL NAME  : Remove Curse
SPELL SYNTAX: Remove <target> <object>
SPELL COST  : 30 SP
DESCRIPTION : This spell serves two different purposes.  First, it
              relieves the target of any curses inflicted ON the
              player around the mud. These are curses like diseases,
              and the like.  Note: Does not include viking. The
              correct syntax to remove a curse like this is:
                      Remove <target players name>

              The second type of curse are curses on objects that
              players carry.  I.e. Weapons and Armour.  To remove
              a cursed item from a player, you use the following
              syntax:
                Remove <target players name> <name of cursed object>
